            <header>
                <h1>Understanding the Breathing Techniques in Demon Slayer</h1>
            </header>
            <p>"Demon Slayer" or "Kimetsu no Yaiba" is a popular anime and manga series that introduces a unique set of swordsmanship skills known as Breathing Techniques. These techniques are derived from various elements of nature, providing the Demon Slayers with enhanced abilities to combat demons.</p>
            <p>Each Breathing Technique is distinct, with its own set of forms, strengths, and weaknesses. Let's explore some of the most iconic techniques:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Water Breathing:</strong> Known for its fluid and flexible movements, Water Breathing mimics the flow of water to adapt to any battle situation.</li>
                <li><strong>Thunder Breathing:</strong> Focuses on quick, lightning-fast attacks. It's known for its speed and precision, often catching enemies off guard.</li>
                <li><strong>Beast Breathing:</strong> A wild and unpredictable style that mirrors the instincts and raw power of a beast. It's used by Inosuke Hashibira, who developed this style himself.</li>
                <li><strong>Sun Breathing:</strong> The original Breathing Technique from which all other techniques are derived. It embodies the strength of the sun and is known for its powerful and versatile attacks.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
    </main>

